poem:
Nametag in the Wabe

'Twas brillig, and the nametag-badge did gyre and gimble in the wabe;
All mimsy were the labels, and the lanyards outgrabe.
Beware the QR-snarl, my friend, the scan that bites and gnaws;
And shun the frumious barcode that gnaws the nametag's laws.
One-two! The letters twirl in Verdigris neon bright;
The badge sprang to life, and printed names with quiet light.
'O frabjous day!' cried the crowd, 'Callooh! Callay!'
For every name wore color, and greetings found their way.
The nametag sang a sibilant tune of welcomes, soft and sly;
A tiny plastic compass, pointing where to go and why.
But soft the hall's murmur rose as meetings came and went;
The badge kept time with handshakes and with smiles it lent.
And through the bustle, its glyphs would dance and flare;
A passport to conversation, printed with careful care.
Thus speaks the nametag: hello, I am here—look, we begin;
A wee herald on a strap, inviting all to spin.

Bittersweet Victory in the Brillig-Moon

'Twas brillig, and the slithy toves did sigh;
We clashed the frumple-snout and nabbed the prize on high;
The win tasted sugar-brine, a gilded, rueful feast,
A frabjous blaze that sang, and yet refused to cease.

We wore the brag-bells proud, with half a grin;
Yet rueful rivets clicked within the skin;
For every sparkling trumpet of triumph's silver tune
We counted the cost beneath the ghostly moon.

The Jubjub hissed a velvet rue, and fluttered round
The banner that billowed high but weighed us down;
We toasted to the victory, bright and clean and proud,
While shadow-snags of memory whispered in the crowd.

So onward we march with flimple feet and wary heart,
The paradox of win and loss not yet undone by art;
Bittersweet the crown we wear, the banner's light and shade;
A victory tasted sweet, with bitter aftertaste laid.

The Promise Kept in Jabberwocky Time

'Twas brillig, and the vow-bells sang at dawn;
Slithy toves murbled through the wabe of night;
I clutched my word-lantern, kept teeth from dawn,
And crossed the jagglet stream of doubt to light.

I gnarfed the shadows, yomped the fogged morass,
Past mome-raths rustle-flecked with dew;
Till at your door I set the glimmering compass,
And spoke the oath that wind and stone knew.

The vow was kept, no snarl of gloom remained;
The yawp of night unknots and yawns goodbye;
We stand where day begins, in light regained—
The promise kept, and we bless the sky.

The Paperclip Chain

'Twas brillig, and the paperclips did gyre and gimble in the wabe;
All mimsy were the nibs and clips, and the borogoves outgrabe the day.
Clip-snack, pop-snack, the links did gleam in moonlit silver thread;
One by one they clasped in rhythm, and the chain woke from its bed.

Clink-clank! the Vorpal Pliers hummed a lilting, dappled tune;
The chain grew long as a lattice, catching lamp-light like a moon.
Snick-snack went every hinge, as each new link did swoop and swing;
Till knots of metal stretched to form a belt of glistening, whispering ring.

The desk became a meadow, paper-froth afloat in air;
Where slip of sheet and stamp of ink were tethered with delicate care.
So let the chain stand watchful, a speckled star in plain sight;
The Jabberwocky of metal, twined about the papers bright.

The Debuggerwock: A Jabberwocky of Error Correction

'Twas codeish dusk, and glith-bugs did gyre;
In thrumble-logs they flickered, bright with fire;
From bracket-wood there rose a patch-song's choir;
The Debuggerwock came, with patch-staff to inspire.

He gnawed the rogue semicolon-snare away;
He straightened braces, tidied the fray;
With lint-winds howling, he sang, "Check it today";
And unit-tests pranced in a metrical relay.

O frabjous fix! O brillig patch of flow!
The code now runs true wherever the wild bugs go;
The CI-sky clears, and the data streams glow;
Thus ends the night of glitches, patched to the bone.

The Evening Breeze in the Wabe

'Twas evening, and the breeze did gyre and gimble in the wabe;
All mimsy hedges slithered slow, and dusk wore a glittering crave;
The borogoves rustled, lilting soft in dew-dust's glow,
While the air went wizzle-wump and tinkled to and fro.

The lamplight blinked with glinting glee as shadows shuffled by;
The twilp of twilight twinkled in the corners of the sky;
O frabjous breeze! O mome-quiet sigh, so cool and keen!
It sweeps the day away and leaves a velvet sheen.

Then, with a final zip and zing, it dances down the lane;
A frumble in the fragrance, a giggle in the grain;
And night unfurls its velvet, as the breeze goes softly on,
To kiss the tired world goodnight till dawn is drawn.
